        <para id="id17179927"><emphasis effect="bold">Mass</emphasis> is defined as:</para>
        <para id="id3843593"><emphasis effect="bold">"a physical quantity expressing the amount of matter in a body"</emphasis>and is measured in kilogram.</para>
        <para id="id17971608">If I therefore say that I weigh 55 kg, I mean that the amount of matter comprising my body comes to 55 kg.</para>
        <para id="id3259881">The mass of an object therefore gives an indication of the amount of matter that an object contains.</para>
        <para id="id3295746">The definition of <emphasis effect="bold">weight</emphasis> is:</para>
        <para id="id3942643">" the vertical force experienced by a mass as the result of gravitation."</para>
        <para id="id17879628">It is important to know that all forms of matter (solid substances, liquids and gases) have mass.</para>
        <para id="id3646477">Explain the difference between mass and weight in your own words.</para>
